&lt;h2 id="relationship">Relationship
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>I&amp;rsquo;ve worked with Open Measures a couple of times over the years. I helped design
their GraphQL API, and was responsible for implementing a graph visualisation
tool to explore politician&amp;rsquo;s social media interactions leading up to the 2020
USA elections (&lt;a class="link" href="https://foundation.mozilla.org/en/blog/fellow-introducing-us-election-twitter-network-graph-tool" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>read more here&lt;/a>)&lt;/p>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://mixmix.nz/p/open-measures/election.png"
width="2754"
height="1372"
srcset="https://mixmix.nz/p/open-measures/election_hu_85a20ddf9d9a5d2f.webp 480w, https://mixmix.nz/p/open-measures/election_hu_bfeff7507a129925.webp 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Graph of social media links to/ from Donald Trump around the 2020 election"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="200"
data-flex-basis="481px"
>
&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I also mentored + trained junior developers working on the project, and later
worked on a more complete version of the graph tool.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Tech I used&lt;/strong>: Vue.js, Pinia, GraphQL, D3&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>